annotationA: Heat shock protein cognate 20 (Hsc20) is a mitochondrial chaperone that facilitates iron sulfur cluster assembly or transfer from IscU to other scaffold proteins. Hsc20 is required for larval growth and cellular iron sensing
annotationB: Adrenodoxin-like protein, mitochondrial; 2 iron, 2 sulfur cluster binding; electron carrier activity; Belongs to the adrenodoxin/putidaredoxin family
